annotationA: Striatin interacting protein, isoform B; Striatin interacting protein (Strip) is an intracellular protein and component of the STRIPAK PP2A protein complex. Strip is involved in hippo signaling, endosome maturation, and microtubule regulation
annotationB: Cerebral cavernous malformation 3 (Ccm3) is a small scaffolding protein. It forms dimers with GckIII, which is essential to CCM3 function and is thought to promote GckIII activity. In the tracheal system, CCM3 is required specifically in terminal cells, and its loss is associated with tube dilation
